transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: My name is Uday. I need a receipt of my prescription.

Speaker 1: No problem at all, sir. Can I get your zip code?

Speaker 2: I used to have a different zip code. Now I get a new zip code. It's 63128.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Becker Place Drive?

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can get a refill for you. Sorry. I thought I was about to sneeze there.

Speaker 2: Okay. Same exact thing as last time on the same card?

Speaker 1: No. I have a different address and different card.

Speaker 2: Oh, it's not Becker Place Drive?

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's Becker Place Drive. Before it's Illinois.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I see that it used to be Illinois, but the current address we have is St. Louis. That's correct, right?

Speaker 1: Yes, yes.

Speaker 2: Okay. You got 30 pills. Is that what you're looking to do again?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Do I get AGV or just a regular?

Speaker 2: You got the AGV the last time. Your last order was AGV.

Speaker 1: Oh, really?

Speaker 2: Yeah. The one from August.

Speaker 1: Okay. I'll get the same one then.

Speaker 2: Is it the MasterCard that ends in 2297?

Speaker 1: No, a different card. Let me give you a new one.

Speaker 2: Okay. I'm ready when you are.

Speaker 1: 52133311838213161.

Speaker 2: Expiration?

Speaker 1: 0129.

Speaker 2: Okay, and the security code?

Speaker 1: 827.

Speaker 2: You want to repeat the card number again?

Speaker 1: No, it didn't go through yet, but I got it validated. It's good. I just updated it on our side, and then I'm going to get your order through here.

Speaker 2: We've actually changed the package. It's the same price, but you're going to get 40 pills. I don't know. I don't remember us doing 30.

Speaker 1: Okay. We're all set, sir. You're good to go. This will ship out on Monday.

Speaker 2: What's the total on that?

Speaker 1: 163.95. That's what your price has been for the last two orders now.

Speaker 2: Okay. All right. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Have a good weekend.

Speaker 2: You too.
